This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it deals with the invertibility of deep neural networks, which is a fundamental concept in machine learning. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with the behavior of neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ReLU-layers, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the robustness of the network, which is a topic in the field of adversarial machine learning, suggesting it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses numerical methods to demonstrate its approach, which could suggest it belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with computational methods.
